name: AudioFileTypeID
desc: Operating system constants that indicate the type of file to be written or a hint about what type of file to expect from data provided.

items.name: var kAudioFileAIFFType: AudioFileTypeID
items.desc: An Audio Interchange File Format (AIFF) file.

items.name: var kAudioFileAIFCType: AudioFileTypeID
items.desc: An Audio Interchange File Format Compressed (AIFF-C) file.

items.name: var kAudioFileNextType: AudioFileTypeID
items.desc: A NeXT or Sun Microsystems file.

items.name: var kAudioFileAAC_ADTSType: AudioFileTypeID
items.desc: An Advanced Audio Coding (AAC) Audio Data Transport Stream (ADTS) file.

items.name: var kAudioFileCAFType: AudioFileTypeID
items.desc: A Core Audio File Format file.

items.name: var kAudioFile3GPType: AudioFileTypeID
items.desc: A 3GPP file, suitable for video content on GSM mobile phones.

items.name: var kAudioFile3GP2Type: AudioFileTypeID
items.desc: A 3GPP2 file, suitable for video content on CDMA mobile phones.

items.name: var kAudioFileAMRType: AudioFileTypeID
items.desc: An AMR (Adaptive Multi-Rate) file suitable for compressed speech.
